                     <interp inst="t18420822-2557-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="theftFromPlace"></interp> for breaking and entering the counting-house of <persName id="t18420822-name-1905" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1905" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1905" type="surname" value="EVANS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1905" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18420822-2557-offence-1 t18420822-name-1905"></join>Thomas Evans</persName> and another, on the <rs id="t18420822-cd-356" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18420822-2557-offence-1 t18420822-cd-356"></join>13th of August</rs>, at <placeName id="t18420822-geo-23">
                        <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18420822-2557-offence-1 t18420822-geo-23"></join>St. Saviour, Southwark</placeName>, and stealing therein 1 pair of spectacles, value 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; 1 hat, value 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; 1 coat, value 6<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; the goods of Thomas Evans; and 3 pairs of compasses, value 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; 2400 pence, and 4800 halfpence, the property of Thomas Evans and another.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420822-name-1906" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1906" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1906" type="surname" value="EVANS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1906" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS EVANS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in partnership with John Lascelles, of Great Guildford-street, St. Saviour, Southwark. On the 13th of August, about half-past six in the morning, I went to the premises, and found the counting-house door open, and the desks forced—I missed out of my desk a pair of spec<lb></lb>tacles, three pairs of compasses, and some loose copper of my own; also some coats, a waistcoat, and hat—the key of the iron-chest, which had been locked up in my desk, was taken out—20<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. in copper belonging to the firm was gone from the chest—I had locked the desk about half-past one the day before—the counting-house is in a yard, at the back of the house of Mr. Burgess, our clerk—it is enclosed by a wall, and there is a door leading to Mr. Lascelles premises from it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420822-name-1907" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1907" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1907" type="surname" value="LASCELLES,"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1907" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN LASCELLES, JUN</persName>
                  </hi>. I live with my father, and am employed in the counting-house—about half-past seven or a quarter to eight o'clock, I shut up the counting-house, locked the door, and took the key—it was all safe at nine o'clock.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420822-name-1908" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1908" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1908" type="surname" value="WELSH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1908" type="given" value="REDMAN"></interp>REDMAN WELSH</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable M</hi> 109.) On the 13th of August, about two o'clock in the morning, I was on duty in Guildford-street, South<lb></lb>wark, and saw the prisoner and another—I followed them into Gravel-lane—they saw me, and separated—I followed, stopped the prisoner, and found 6<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 3 1/2 <hi rend="italic">d</hi>. in copper, three pairs of compasses, a pair of spectacles, and case</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184208220275"></xptr>
               <p>on him—he was wearing a coat, waistcoat, and hat, which I now pro<lb></lb>duce—be had them on.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. EVANS</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined</hi>. This is my coat and waistcoat—they were taken from a box—the lock of the door appeared to have been picked—the other articles are mine.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420822-name-1909" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1909" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1909" type="surname" value="LEWIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1909" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES LEWIS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. I took these articles off the pri<lb></lb>soner's back.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420822-name-1910" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1910" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1910" type="surname" value="MILLS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1910" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN MILLS</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable M</hi> 31.) I found a coat in the prosecutor's counting-house—I made the prisoner try it on—it appeared to fit him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence</hi>. It is not ray coat; I was coming from Horseley-down-stairs, went into a public-house, and bought the things of a man who owned them; I saw the two policemen drinking together when they stopped me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420822-name-1911" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1911" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1911" type="surname" value="WELSH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1911" type="given" value="REDMAN"></interp>REDMAN WELSH</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined</hi>. We stopped him 150 yards from the counting-house—we were not drinking—there is no public-house in the street.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. A young gentleman in the street with them had got a bottle.</p>
